5/15/00
  Attended the SCTE API group conference meeting:
    - 6201 port will be used for all API exchange
    - added informative statement that the splicer is expected to be able
      to support connections no less than 3 times the number of channels.
    - found out that the time() specified in SpliceRequest message is meant
      to be the actual splice time.  The ad server will derive this from the
      cue message.  The 300 - 600 msec requirement is for the data delivery,
      not the display time.
    - requested to change "video must start 300 - 600 msec ..." to
      "ad stream must start ..."
    - we can assume that the ad server should be reasonable in the data
      delivery timing.  In the back-to-back ad case, we should not allow
      too much overlap.  When there is a gap, we can insert black frames.


5/18/00
  Finally found the bug which cause all the picture break problem.  Its in
  editBits().  When bitPos=0, we should not do clrU and update current word!

  After the bug is fixed, the new BitBuf module are checked in into ClearCase.

  However, the code will not compile if PCR_PID or VBI flags are turn on.
  Need to come back and fix this issue in the next commit.

  PCR_PID and VBI modes supported now.


